organic_results.title: Sex-role identification, ability, and achievement among high school girls
organic_results.snippet: This paper finds a significant relationship between a non-traditional, personal-fulfillment-(" masculine") oriented female sex-role perception and ability. With IQ controlled, however, the more non-traditional the orientation of girls' sex-role perception, the lower the academic achievement (class standing). Conversely, the more traditional the sex-role identification, the higher the class rank. Moreover, the data suggest a positive relationship between a non-traditional, personal-fulfillment orientation and higher educational aspirations.
